<DOC sysid="rbmt-4" docid="denik.cz/2012/12/01/62159" genre="news" origlang="cs">
<h1>
<seg id="1">Šimon Ornest: In our concerts we want to accumulate positive energy</seg>
</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">It is said that in little less than one month is going to arrive the end of the world, what does he opine on that?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3">It is only one out of so much other alarmist news that, which, like to grab each other.</seg>
<seg id="4">The group of music The Tap Tap rather likes us to do jokes on this and we like to say that we are the only group of music of the world that manages to bring sufficient positive energy together to postpone the end of the world or to prevent it.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5">Besides, in December you really organize a project original: three concerts against the end of the world.</seg>
<seg id="6">Can it explain it to our readers?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7">It is a charitable state act that we have been planning since two years ago.</seg>
<seg id="8">We decide to make use of the marketing potential that has the end of the Mayan calendar enunciated for the 21st of December to the 11:10 of the morning.</seg>
<seg id="9">On the previous day, on the 20th of December at 21 o'clock, we will organize 3 simultaneous concerts in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.</seg>
<seg id="10">They will finish approximately at the same hour in which it finishes the Mayan calendar in the Kiribati island, in the Pacific Ocean, 12 hours in front of our hourly area.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="11">To whom did this idea occur?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="12">At first it was my idea, afterwards we all kept forging the project together with our designer Honza Augusta.</seg>
<seg id="13">Besides wanting to bring sufficient positive energy together and to prevent the end of the world, we also want to reflect, together with the society, on the state in which we will leave the world to our children.</seg>
<seg id="14">On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar we have also created a unique collection of articles: boots, T-shirts, bags exchanges and key ring originals against the end of the world that can be acquired in www.e-tap.cz, another way of supporting us.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="15">The group The Tap Tap, together with other interpreters, also sang the called hymn against the end of the world, which is entitled "End of the world, canceled".</seg>
<seg id="16">At present it is very popular in YouTube, will it be able to be heard in the charitable concerts?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="17">Clear that yes, and the last one will be exactly, good, as long as everything comes out well and the world does not run out...</seg>
<seg id="18">All the interpreters will sing it at the same time in the three concerts.</seg>
<seg id="19">The hymns will be linked among themselves simultaneously thanks to the special retransmission live in the Czech Television.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="20">Tomás Hanák has written the letter of this song and protagonist of Jesus interprets the paper in the video clip, where he also sings Xindl X...</seg>
<seg id="21">How did this collaboration rise up?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="22">We work together even with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, apart from organizing many charitable acts and concerts...</seg>
<seg id="23">We put all our determination in taking part in this project.</seg>
<seg id="24">It has been proved that it interests most of them and it amuses them to work with us.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="25">What will the money raised in the concerts against the end of the world be destined for?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="26">To equipment for the educational center without barriers Studeo, which we take to term in its sixth consecutive year with the civil association Tap in Jedličkův ústav.</seg>
<seg id="27">The pupils of the school of Jedličkův ústav receive regularly the visit of teachers with whom they carry out amusing and interesting activities.</seg>
<seg id="28">The pupils do not have sufficient economic means to pay the teachers and we make an efuerzo to make it possible.</seg>
<seg id="29">Within the framework of the ending of the works in Jedličkův ústav, there will be an independent building to which we will move with this project.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="30">In every concert several groups and interpreters act.</seg>
<seg id="31">Which are the criteria of selection?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="32">We try to elaborate a program that is an appeal for all the generations, the children included.</seg>
<seg id="33">For example, in Prague Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, will act Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.</seg>
<seg id="34">In order to obtain more detailed information, you can consult www.kpks.cz.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="35">Do you plan any other similar "spectacular action" in the future?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="36">In May we, Pražské jaro, will act for the first time in the festival, so we will here probably prepare an attractive program with interesting guests.</seg>
<seg id="37">The year that he comes also we would like to be due in the Bohemian National Hall of New York and I, personally, taking advantage of our being in the United States, would like to complete it with performances in Washington and in Chicago.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="38">Your plans abroad are not precisely minimalist, until now you have acted for example in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.</seg>
<seg id="39">The Tap Tap is, however, a group formed by people with disability.</seg>
<seg id="40">How is it the logistics and the organization of these journeys?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="41">It is not so difficult how it can seem at first sight.</seg>
<seg id="42">There are five members in electrical wheelchair, the chairs must travel in the compartment for luggages and besides we take a lot of weight, the boxes with the instruments...</seg>
<seg id="43">However, until now we have fixed them to ourselves well. ČSA and British Airways were perfectly preparations, thing that does not stop surprising me.</seg>
<seg id="44">Even in Moscow, of where we have gone back not long ago, everything came out troublefree.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="45">Thanks to the exits you can compare the different attitudes of the society towards the disabled ones and other aspects to the foreigner.</seg>
<seg id="46">What have you found until now?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="47">In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia we have been witnesses that, in the east, a lot of path remains because it goes.</seg>
<seg id="48">Unlike Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there it keeps not being frequent that a person is displaced by the town center in an electrical wheelchair alone.</seg>
<seg id="49">Is not, something as ordinary as it is, for example, to give somebody preference in wheelchair in elevator, there.</seg>
<seg id="50">For luck, has been created a civil association that makes an effort for tematizar the problems of the people with disability.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="51">In which aspects must we take example of more advanced countries?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="52">There are many aspects in those that go at the back...</seg>
<seg id="53">But it is important to mention that the perfection and the improvement of the situation always depends on the people that it affects directly.</seg>
<seg id="54">In London and in Madrid it is very normal that the people with a severe disability move for its account in public and can go to the service, to the museum, where it wants...</seg>
<seg id="55">But it is not very common that a great number of people with disability take part in the social life in an active way, in this aspect, with The Tap Tap we go a little in front!</seg>
<seg id="56">A society respectful or without barriers is a thing, but she when it arrives the moment in which eminent sportsmen, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers rise up, will really start to change everything.</seg>
<seg id="57">Until now, they are cases isolated from people who have a great will power.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="58">The group The Tap Tap is at present very popular, but if we look some years behind, what led you to form the group in 1998?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="59">I entered as educator in Jedličkův ústav, where it had many young people around me that they wanted to dedicate themselves to something.</seg>
<seg id="60">And since I am musical, I touch, among others, the saxophone, I founded an amateurish group with a work colleague.</seg>
<seg id="61">And with time, as our moderator says Láďa Angelovič, a little lost us controls (laughters).</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="62">However, the popularity did not arrive until these last years, or do I make a mistake?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="63">It is truth which the fact that it connected with famous singers and it also worked actively to promote the group helped us quite a lot.</seg>
<seg id="64">We arrive to the conclusion that the work that is not seen, is as if it did not exist.</seg>
<seg id="65">Thanks to the helps of the European Union, we can allow ourselves teaching staff of quality, equipment, etc besides.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="66">Did you have intention of arriving so far with The Tap Tap?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="67">From the principle I saw the potential that there was, which can be done something in another way.</seg>
<seg id="68">The show business is full of things that are seemed the some ones to the other ones.</seg>
<seg id="69">It is logical, to its way, all what is new is received with caution and takes it a lot of time to be accepted.</seg>
<seg id="70">There are few extraordinary things, but I dare to say that The Tap Tap is one of them.</seg>
<seg id="71">The impression of somebody that sees us for the first time is clearly the pity, is a natural reaction...</seg>
<seg id="72">But the pity is totally superfluous because the people with disability are not neglected beings who suffer and of which we must have pity.</seg>
<seg id="73">There are people who are capable of living a full life and developing, with the condition, of course, that it has the necessary means.</seg>
<seg id="74">I always say that if something comes out well for them to people with disability, then, it is not only one advance for them, but for all the society.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="75">Did the fact that you are a demanding head, as he describes him many people, help?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="76">If we want to do a work of quality, we have to be rigorous in many aspects and to require a certain discipline.</seg>
<seg id="77">I think that it is completely normal.</seg>
<seg id="78">Some people arrive with a romantic vision and with the head in the clouds and when they find out that have to go two days to rehearse, to go to the preparatory test and to pass a lot of time traveling and in concerts, the initial euphoria abandons them quickly.</seg>
<seg id="79">But like this it is, in every group that it wants to work and to obtain something, how it works everywhere.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="80">At present the group The Tap Tap has twenty members.</seg>
<seg id="81">How many of them were already in the beginnings of the year 1998?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="82">Only one: Láďa Angelovič.</seg>
<seg id="83">We are an open group, the people enter and goes out, cannot be prevented.</seg>
<seg id="84">The one who has will and desires will always find the open doors</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="85">It will be the day before the expected end of the world, on Thursday 20.12.2012 at 21 o'clock</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="86">It will take place in the Incheba Arena of Prague, in Fléda de Brno and in Plynojem in Ostrava and 12 groups and other musicians will share the Czech Republic</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="87">The three cities will be connected at the end of the evening party through video conference to sing together the song of the group The Tap Tap "End of the world, canceled"</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="88">The goal of the concert is to bring the necessary resources together to finance multifunctional equipment of the educational center without barriers STUDEO in Jedličkův ústav of Prague, whose cost rises at 25 million Czech crowns.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="89">The entered to the concert slope 400 CZK and the children until 12 years have free entry in the sale option anticipated in Bohemiaticket</seg>
</p>
